Media notes: Sleepy Creek road 0.5 miles west of ranger station. "Adult male Northern Cardinal giving chip calls. Habitat: Deciduous woods. Distance: 9 meters. Equipment note: Telinga Pro 7 HPF on."

Locality: Picayune Strand SF--Belle Mead Horse Trail

Media notes: Nearly dark. Bird calling from bushes after I apparently disturbed it by walking by. Moving from spot to spot on occasion, but never far.
Observation Details: One at the feeders at the outset. Two (perhaps one) rustled then called from shrubs in the draw within a few meters of me as I walked by. Recorded with Merlin on an iPhone using its internal mic and also with a Zoom F3 and Rode NTG2 shotgun mic. No headphones, so I couldn't be sure the mic was optimally positioned or if I was generating handling noise. The evening was quiet overall, so it could make for an interesting experiment. The iPhone recording and one of the Zoom/Rode recordings overlap.

Media notes: Alarm notes from a male cardinal in response to a Gray Ratsnake that was in the bush where their nest was.
